<DOC><DOCNO> AP880923-0002 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-23-88 0605EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--PrisonBlunder     09-23 0159</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Prison Blunder,0164</SECOND><HEAD>Guards Unwittingly Help Murder Suspect Escape</HEAD><DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A murder suspect who broke hisleg jumping to freedom from a prison wall persuaded guards he wasonly visiting the prison and they unwittingly helped him escape,police said.   Police spokesman Frans Malherbe said police were investigatingthe Aug. 28 escape from Johannesburg's Diepkloof Prison by MichaelMathebula, 24, who was accused of murder and rape.   Guards found Mathebula lying beside the prison wall and believedhis story that he was a visitor who broke his leg jumping from abus, police said Thursday.   The guards arranged for an ambulance to take Mathebula toBaragwanath Hospital in Soweto, where he vanished after beingtreated, police said.   ``If anyone is found to have been negligent, steps will be takenagainst him,'' Malherbe said.   Mathebula also is wanted in the black homeland of Bophuthatswanaon murder charges and four counts of escaping from police custody.</TEXT></DOC>